===Etymology===
According to STEDT, from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*tsuk ~ tsik||to build}}; cognate with {{cog|bo|རྩིག||to build}}, {{cog|tbq-lob-pro|*ʔtsukᴴ||to build}} (whence {{cog|my|ဆောက်||to build}}).

On the other hand, {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} derives this from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*truk}}, whence also {{cog|bo|རྡུག||to conquer; to vanquish}} and {{cog|my|တိုက်||to dash against; to bump against}}. STEDT derives the {{cog|bo|-}} word from {{cog|tbq-pro|*m/r-tuk||cut; knock; pound}}.

